nodes.title: Note. v1.4 Dev
widgets_values:
RULE 1: Seed - is everything!

MODEL:
Dev model uses 20+ steps.

PARAMETERS:
CFG (1-7) - lower values give more motion, high values give less motion and overcooced look.
CRF (10-30) - compression, high values give more motion and lower the output quality.
FRate (1-25) - high values give more motion.

CAMERA CONTROL:
Camera Steps (1-4) - sets the initial vector for camera movement. Use 2 steps. If camera doesn't move right - see RULE 1 and/or increase steps.
Camera Animation Value (5-30) - high values give more camera motion. 10 is good start point (Actually, I wouldn't touch this parameter - it has almost no effect on the result. Instead - use Camera Steps, it has huge impact to camera motion). 

PROMPTING:
You can use Florens prompt. You can Add your own prompt To Florence. You can use your own prompt without Florence (there is a Switcher).
There is "standart" negative prompt, but you can Add specific to it.


UPSCALER:
Dev model is slower than Dist - so you can use lowres pass and then upscaler pass (it uses Flow Edit tech).
